cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing tasks such as identifying implicit discourse relations. Additionally, the use of deep learning methods and neural networks further supports this categorization. 

The paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of deep learning models. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the task of understanding the meaning of text, which is a core problem in AI. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the classification of implicit discourse relations, which is a task that can be useful in information retrieval systems.
